    "summary": "During my PhD at Maastricht University, I focused on the relationship between prenatal maternal stress and adult psychopathology. My main interest was directed towards the biological mechanisms that may explain the increased prevalence of affective disorders in prenatally stressed subjects. \n\nAs a post-doc and assistant professor, as a collaboration between the various divisions within MHeNs and the Department of Psychiatry and Psychotherapy at the University of W\u00fcrzburg in Germany, I moved towards investigating the role of gene x environment (GxE) interactions, and their underlying epigenetic mechanisms, in the pathophysiology of psychiatric and neurodegenerative disorders like depression, panic disorder and Alzheimer\u2019s disease. \nPresently, I am head of the Section Fundamental Neuroscience within the Department of Psychiatry and Neuropsychology. Furthermore, I am heading the Neuroepigenetics group within division 3 of MHeNs, as well as the Research Line Epigenetic Programming of Brain Development, Neural Plasticity and Networks at the University of W\u00fcrzburg, addressing the role of epigenetic processes in mental health and disease (in a lifelong perspective). Moreover, I am coordinator of the Research Master Specialisation Fundamental Neuroscience (FN).\n\nCurrently, I also coordinate the H2020 JPND project EPI-AD, a large European project involving various pioneering epigenetic research labs including Maastricht (the Netherlands), Exeter (UK), Bonn, Wuerzburg (Germany), Luxembourg (Luxembourg) and Barcelona (Spain), which studies the role of epigenetic dysregulation in the brainstem in Alzheimer\u2019s Disease (www.epi-ad-eu).\n\nTeaching\nCoordinator Research Master Specialisation Fundamental Neuroscience (FN); lecturing, tutoring and course planning (Maastricht University).\n\nPulications: see http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/sites/entrez?term=van%20den%20hove%20d[Author]\n\nSpecialties: Languages:\nDutch (native), English (very good), German (good), French (beginner)\n\nComputing: \nAnalySIS, Ethovision, Excel, Powerpoint, Sigmaplot, Sigmastat, SPSS, Word",
